data.name: Menu_OpenHauptwerkOrgan.ToolTipText
data.value:
Select and load an ODF file using a standard Windows File-Open Dialog. Windows uses the last opened ODF's directory as the starting place to locate this ODF.
If there is a modified but unsaved ODF currently loaded, prompts to save it before opening a new one.

data.name: Menu_ReComputeSections.ToolTipText
data.value: AECHO will scan the entire ODF, indentifying all Sections, and displaying in the Descriptive Text Box each Section's ID #, Starting & Ending positions, Starting & Ending Line Numbers, and Name, in the order found. Upon completion, the main display will be positioned to the DisplayPage Section.

data.name: Menu_CouplersCode.ToolTipText
data.value: Displays an independant Window, which decodes Integer Coupler Codes into their Sources, Destinations, and Types; it also translates choices of Source / Destination / Type into the corresponding internal HW code.

data.name: Menu_FollowASample.ToolTipText
data.value: Invokes an independant Window that traces data related to a (sound) SampleID, presenting this data on a single consolidated form. It displays the Installation Package ID, Filename, Pitch Specification Method Code, Pitch Rank Base, Pitch Normal MIDI Note, Pitch Exact Sample Pitch, License Info, and Pipe Sound Engine 01 Attack Sample.

data.name: Status_RowTypeVal.ToolTipText
data.value: The type of the Row containing the current Line: NA - No ODF XML Header - the opening header of an ODF ODF Start-Tag - the opening <Haupterk...> tag ODF End-Tag - the closing </Hauptwerk> tag Gen Sec Data - content inside the _General Section Sec Start-Tag - Section Start <ObjectList...> Sec End-Tag - Section End </ObjectList> Record - <o>...</o> content within a Section
